Package: superml
Type: Package
Title: Various handy wrappers functions like scikit-learn to speed up machine learning tasks in R
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Manish Saraswat
Maintainer: Manish Saraswat <manish06saraswat@gmail.com>
Description: This package intends to ease the process of training machine learning models in R. 
    The idea is to provide a standard interface to users who use both R and Python since they often struggle in remembering the code syntax in R.
    This package will help users switch quickly and do their day to day work.    
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends:
    R(>= 3.4)
Imports:
    tm(>= 0.7),
    ranger(>= 0.9),
    xgboost(>= 0.6),
    data.table(>= 1.10.4.3),
    caret(>= 6.0.78),
    parallel(>= 3.4.3),
    glmnet(>= 2.0.16),
    R6(>= 2.2.2),
    assertthat(>= 0.2.0)
Suggests:
    knitr,
    rlang,
    testthat
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
